title: [Bloodriven Village, River Bank]
description: Feeding in through the Locksmehr River to the south, dark waters flow north from the wide watercourse.  The shore is narrow, and the only pathway is a muddy trail leading up the river bank.

Small tributaries feed into the Locksmehr River, creating a wide watercourse filled with swiftly flowing dark waters that eventually empty into Darkstone Bay.  The narrow shoreline follows the river's edge, the newly shorn grasses providing a rundown hovel in the distance, while nearer at hand a muddy trail provides the only pathway up the riverbank to the city gates.

Small frozen tributaries feed into the Locksmehr River, creating a wide solid watercourse filled with dark ice that leads into Darkstone Bay. The narrow shoreline follows the river's edge, the barren ground providing a rundown hovel in the distance, while nearer at hand a ice and mud-covered trail provides the only pathway up the riverbank to the city gates.
